
------------------------- CREATING A REPO ON GITHUB ON PUSHING LOCAL CODE ------------------------------------------------------

1) Create a new repository on github GUI (website)
		- Provide repo name
		- description
		- License

2) Obtain the url for repo

3) Open terminal and cd to the project directory

4) GIT Commands (Initial Code Push):
	i)   git init
	ii)  git add .
	iii) git pull <url>
	iv)  git commit -m "<message/version>"
	v)   git remote add <repo-name> <url>
	vi)  git push --set-upstream <repo-name> <branch-name/master/dev etc.>               (--set-upstream is required only for first time pushing to the repo)

5) for merging : (server code and local code are not in synch , i,e, not in same commit numbers)
	git pull <repo-name> <branch-name> --allow-unrelated-hitories


